<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[360,486,151,175]" name="Philippines" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[502,622,151,175]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.94" metricValueMin="0.96" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="145.0" valueMax="194.0" valueMin="96.0">96–194 m</quantity>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Leloup" box="[633,777,151,175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Leloup, E. (1981) Resultats des campagnes Musorstom I: Philippines (18 - 28 Mars 1976): Mollusques: Polyplacophores. Memoires Orstom, 91, 317 - 323." type="journal article" year="1981">
Leloup 
<number box="[720,777,151,175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[842,934,152,175]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[950,1083,151,175]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.335" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="4.17" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="633.5" valueMax="850.0" valueMin="417.0">417–850 m</quantity>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[1095,1256,151,175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2001) Deep-sea chitons (Mollusca, Polyplacophora) from sunken wood off New Caledonia and Vanuatu. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, 185, 39 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">
Sirenko, 
<number box="[1197,1256,151,175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; this study) and now also the 
<collectingCountry box="[307,496,188,212]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[514,644,188,212]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.775" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.05" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="577.5" valueMax="650.0" valueMin="505.0">505-650 m</quantity>
). The present material confirms and expands the known distribution. Found living and feeding on sunken terrestrial plant remains.
</paragraph>
