<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is known from the juvenile 
<typeStatus box="[777,875,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">holotype</typeStatus>
and a series of 
<specimenCount box="[1051,1142,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="adult">
<number box="[1051,1079,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="10.0">10</number>
adult
</specimenCount>
specimens collected from the same small area, Verde Passage, Luzon, 
<collectingCountry box="[660,786,295,319]" name="Philippines" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas" box="[803,929,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Kaas, P. (1982) Leptochiton species (Polyplacophora: Leptochitonidae) of the Musorstom 1 (1976) and 2 (1980) Philippines expeditions. Basteria, 46, 87 - 92." type="journal article" year="1982">
Kaas 
<number box="[869,929,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[951,1121,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2001) Deep-sea chitons (Mollusca, Polyplacophora) from sunken wood off New Caledonia and Vanuatu. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, 185, 39 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">
Sirenko (
<number box="[1055,1113,295,319]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,304,333,356]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[319,419,332,356]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" precision="555" value="-16.54">
<number box="[319,385,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="16.54">16.54</number>
° S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[432,546,332,356]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" precision="555" value="168.2">
<number box="[432,512,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="168.2">168.20</number>
° E
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[558,688,332,356]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.735" metricValueMax="4.88" metricValueMin="4.59" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="473.5" valueMax="488.0" valueMin="459.0">459–488 m</quantity>
), which is very close to the additional localities reported here. The specimens reported here are the deepest records for the species. Several stations (Boa 
<number box="[1158,1172,367,391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1.0">1</number>
sta. CP 
<number box="[1267,1325,367,391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2465.0">2465</number>
, CP 
<number box="[1374,1432,367,391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2466.0">2466</number>
, CP 
<number box="[186,243,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2435.0">2435</number>
) extend the maximum depth to 
<quantity box="[628,752,404,428]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.35" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.7" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="835.0" valueMax="900.0" valueMin="770.0">770–900m</quantity>
; the previously reported maximum depth was 
<quantity box="[1304,1436,404,428]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.735" metricValueMax="4.88" metricValueMin="4.59" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="473.5" valueMax="488.0" valueMin="459.0">459–488 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[158,314,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2001) Deep-sea chitons (Mollusca, Polyplacophora) from sunken wood off New Caledonia and Vanuatu. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, 185, 39 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">
Sirenko 
<number box="[254,314,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
